jalse.entities

Class EntitySet

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractSet<Entity>
        • jalse.entities.EntitySet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Entity>, java.util.Collection<Entity>, java.util.Set<Entity>

    public class EntitySet
extends java.util.AbstractSet<Entity>
    An EntitySet is a thread-safe Set implementation for Entity. An EntitySet follows the same pattern defined in EntityContainer but offers a collections based implementation (so it may be used more generically).

    EntitySet can take a delegate EntityContainer to supply to EntityEvent. Entity updates will trigger these events using EntityListener.

    By default EntitySet will use DefaultEntityFactory with no delegate container.
    Author:
    Elliot Ford
